. 1027","children":[],"tail":", provided that: "},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/115/52/tIII/s306"},"text":"“The amendments made by this title [see ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/115/52/s301/a"},"text":"section 301(a) of Pub. L. 115–52","children":[],"tail":", set out as a Short Title of 2017 Amendment note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t21/s301"},"text":"section 301 of this title","children":[],"tail":"] shall take effect on "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2017-10-01"},"text":"October 1, 2017","children":[],"tail":", or the date of the enactment of this Act ["},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2017-08-18"},"text":"Aug. 18, 2017","children":[],"tail":"], whichever is later, except that fees under part 7 of subchapter C of chapter VII of the Federal Food, Drug, and Cosmetic Act ["},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t21/s379j–41"},"text":"21 U.S.C. 379j–41","children":[],"tail":" et seq.] shall be assessed for all abbreviated new drug applications received on or after "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2017-10-01"},"text":"October 1, 2017","children":[],"tail":", regardless of the date of the enactment of this Act.”"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"miscellaneous","id":"id145d41e7-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective and Termination Dates","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/180/dF/tIII/s3004/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 117–180, div. F, title III, § 3004(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2022-09-30"},"text":"Sept. 30, 2022","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/136/2159"},"text":"136 Stat. 2159","children":[],"tail":", provided that: "},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/117/180/dF/tIII/s3004/a"},"text":"“Sections 744A and 744B of the Federal Food, Drug, an